<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="182" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[132,775,1907,2030]" box="[132,232,1907,1933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[132,775,1907,2030]" lastBlockId="5.[813,1455,1078,1456]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">
Delamare Debouteville first used the combination 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Delamare Debouteville 1951 a:" authorityYear="1074" class="Collembola" family="Paronellidae" genus="Paronella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beguei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Paronella beguei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 1948 referring to a paronellid found together with termites. This first mention of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Delamare Debouteville 1951 a:" authorityYear="1074" box="[474,565,2003,2029]" class="Collembola" family="Paronellidae" genus="Paronella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beguei">
<emphasis box="[474,565,2003,2029]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">P. beguei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
included neither a morphological description nor drawings and therefore it is a 
<emphasis box="[831,982,1110,1136]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">nomen nudum</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[813,1455,1078,1456]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">
The only other significant citations for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Delamare Debouteville 1951 a:" authorityYear="1074" box="[1261,1351,1142,1168]" class="Collembola" family="Paronellidae" genus="Paronella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beguei">
<emphasis box="[1261,1351,1142,1168]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">P. beguei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are those of Delamare Debouteville (1951b), concerning its ecology, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mitra" box="[860,1014,1206,1232]" firstAuthor="Mitra" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" pagination="105 - 116" refId="ref14625" refString="MITRA S. K. 2002 c. - Status of Dicranocentruga Wray, 1953 with the description of a new species (Collembola: Entomobryidae). Records of the Zoological Survey of India 100: 105 - 116." type="journal article" year="2002" yearSuffix="c">Mitra (2002c)</bibRefCitation>
in which the author transfers the species to the genus 
<emphasis box="[952,1124,1238,1263]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Dicranocentruga</emphasis>
Wray, 1953.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[813,1455,1078,1456]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">
We assign this species to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Soto-Adames &amp; Bellini" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[1113,1256,1269,1295]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Trogolaphysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1113,1256,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Trogolaphysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on mucro shape, which is typical for the genus, short and bearing 4 teeth, and the relatively long antennae. Otherwise, this is a well-marked species, unique among African forms in having a distinctive color pattern (
<figureCitation box="[1213,1291,1397,1424]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="14.[132,143,1917,1935]" captionTargetBox="[271,1322,222,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[261,1341,211,1857]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIG. 5. — A, Trogolaphysa grassei (Delamare Debouteville, 1952) n. comb.hind claw form Delamare-Deboutteville (1952);B, T. ghesquierei (Marlier,1945) n. comb. hind claw from Marlier (1945);C, T. fuelleborni n. comb.hind claw from Börner (1903); D, T.monomaculata, hind claw from Barra (1969);E, L. flava, hind claw from Carpenter (1916); F, T. monomaculata, mucro from Barra (1969); G, T. vivieni, mucro from Barra (1969); H, T. beguei (Delamare Debouteville, 1951) n. comb, hind claw complex, modified from Delamare Deboutteville (1951a); I, T. lamottei (Delamare Debouteville,1950) n. comb.habitus, modified from Delamare Deboutteville (1950b); J, T. beguei n. comb. habitus, modified from Delamare Deboutteville (1951a)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3738239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3738239/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Fig. 5J</figureCitation>
) and truncate unguiculus (
<figureCitation box="[953,1043,1429,1456]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="14.[132,143,1917,1935]" captionTargetBox="[271,1322,222,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[261,1341,211,1857]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIG. 5. — A, Trogolaphysa grassei (Delamare Debouteville, 1952) n. comb.hind claw form Delamare-Deboutteville (1952);B, T. ghesquierei (Marlier,1945) n. comb. hind claw from Marlier (1945);C, T. fuelleborni n. comb.hind claw from Börner (1903); D, T.monomaculata, hind claw from Barra (1969);E, L. flava, hind claw from Carpenter (1916); F, T. monomaculata, mucro from Barra (1969); G, T. vivieni, mucro from Barra (1969); H, T. beguei (Delamare Debouteville, 1951) n. comb, hind claw complex, modified from Delamare Deboutteville (1951a); I, T. lamottei (Delamare Debouteville,1950) n. comb.habitus, modified from Delamare Deboutteville (1950b); J, T. beguei n. comb. habitus, modified from Delamare Deboutteville (1951a)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3738239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3738239/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Fig. 5H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
